The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Melbourne, July 15 (PTI): Three more Indians have reportedly disappeared in New Zealand, on their way to Sydney, to see the Pope on the World Youth Day celebrations.          
	This has brought the number of missing Catholics to 39, prompting authorities to investigate the possibility of an immigration scam. An Indian taxi driver had spoken to the missing men, aged between 17 and 35, about their plans and had informed the New Zealand Sikh Society, media reports said.                  
	 Dubai (PTI): Bahrain will soon offer visas to Indians on their arrival. This move is expected to attract a major chunk of tourists from the subcontinent to the Gulf country, the interior ministry announced. The tourists should carry a valid passport, a return ticket and produce either hotel reservation details or family contacts in the country. Visas will initially be offered for two weeks.                   
	 Bangalore (PTI): A sports-enthusiast was duped of about Rs 2.5 lakh by a website through which he had booked tickets to China to watch the Beijing Olympics, police said on Tuesday.                   
	 London (PTI): A 19-year-old Briton has confessed to the murder of two elderly women of Indian origin and will be sentenced on July 30. Rashmi Badiani, 56, and Radhaben Chauhan were murdered after the killer broke into their room but found nothing to steal.                  
	Kochi (PTI): A false warning of a bomb in Lourdes Hospital turned out to be a prank by a 10-year-old boy, who later confessed that he had made the call after his mother refused to take him to visit a relative admitted in the hospital.                  
	 Lakhimpur Kheri (PTI): Three members of a family, including an infant, were hacked to death in a village here. The murdered couple had apparently eloped two years ago. Umakant, who had allegedly eloped with the girl from the same village as him and married her about two years ago, was returning home with his family when the girls family members attacked and killed them, police said.                                                                                                                         
